---
---

<section class="philosophy-section" aria-labelledby="philosophy-heading" data-gsap="reveal">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="philosophy-inner">
      <!-- Display quote -->
      <div class="philosophy-quote-wrap">
        <div class="philosophy-rule" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <blockquote class="philosophy-quote">
          Photography, for us, is three things at once: a discipline worth mastering, a language for documenting the world we live in, and a reason to leave the house and find your people.
        </blockquote>
        <div class="philosophy-rule" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      </div>

      <!-- Mission + Vision -->
      <div class="philosophy-grid">
        <div class="philosophy-col">
          <div class="philosophy-kicker">Mission</div>
          <h3 class="philosophy-heading" id="philosophy-heading">To build a photography community where every member can learn, grow, and contribute.</h3>
          <p class="philosophy-body">Bhopal Camera Club exists for photographers at every stage of the craft — the beginner who just picked up their first camera, and the seasoned practitioner who wants to keep growing. We believe that photography learned in community is photography learned more deeply.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="philosophy-col">
          <div class="philosophy-kicker">Vision</div>
          <h3 class="philosophy-heading">To be the most trusted visual record of Bhopal — a living archive of the city through the eyes of its photographers.</h3>
          <p class="philosophy-body">Every photowalk we conduct, every image shared in our gallery, every workshop we run adds another layer to a collective document of Bhopal. Over decades, this archive will be something of genuine historical value to this city.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Purpose tags -->
      <div class="philosophy-tags" role="list">
        <span class="philosophy-tag" role="listitem">Photography as Learning</span>
        <span class="philosophy-tag" role="listitem">Photography as Documentation</span>
        <span class="philosophy-tag" role="listitem">Photography as Friendship</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
.philosophy-section {
  background: var(--surface-0);
  border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline);
  padding: 72px 0;
}
.philosophy-inner {
  max-width: 960px;
  margin: 0 auto;
}

/* Display quote */
.philosophy-quote-wrap {
  text-align: center;
  margin-bottom: 64px;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 32px;
}
.philosophy-rule {
  width: 40px;
  height: 1px;
  background: var(--gold-500);
}
.philosophy-quote {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 34px);
  font-weight: 300;
  letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  line-height: 1.5;
  color: var(--ink-900);
  max-width: 780px;
  font-style: normal;
  text-wrap: pretty;
}

/* Mission / Vision grid */
.philosophy-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  gap: 64px;
  margin-bottom: 56px;
}
.philosophy-kicker {
  font-size: 10px;
  letter-spacing: 0.22em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--gold-600);
  font-weight: 600;
  margin-bottom: 20px;
  font-family: var(--font-body);
}
.philosophy-heading {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: 22px;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  line-height: 1.2;
  margin-bottom: 16px;
  color: var(--ink-900);
}
.philosophy-body {
  font-size: 15px;
  line-height: 1.85;
  color: var(--ink-600);
}

/* Tags */
.philosophy-tags {
  display: flex;
  gap: 12px;
  justify-content: center;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
}
.philosophy-tag {
  font-size: 12px;
  letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
  padding: 8px 18px;
  color: var(--ink-600);
  font-family: var(--font-body);
}

/* Responsive */
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .philosophy-section {
    padding: 48px 0;
  }
  .philosophy-grid {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 40px;
  }
  .philosophy-quote {
    font-size: clamp(20px, 5vw, 28px);
  }
}
</style>
